🚀 Ultimate Project Setup Guide
This document contains everything you need to set up, run, and test this MERN backend on any computer.

1️⃣ Phase 1: Preparation (Do this once)
Install Node.js:

Download and install the LTS version from nodejs.org.
Verify installation by opening a terminal and typing: node -v
Get the Project Files:

Copy your backend folder to the new computer.
Do NOT copy the node_modules folder (it's too big and specific to your old PC).
2️⃣ Phase 2: Installation
Open Terminal:

Navigate to your project folder:
bash
cd path/to/backend
Install Dependencies (The Golden Command):

Run this exact command to install all required packages with stable versions:
bash
npm install express@5 cors dotenv@16 mongoose@8 node-fetch@3
Set Up Environment Variables:

Create a new file named 
.env
 in the backend folder.
Paste the following content into it:
env
PORT=3000
MONGO_URI=mongodb+srv://admin:admin123@cluster0.nmxweba.mongodb.net/books_db?appName=Cluster0
3️⃣ Phase 3: Running the Server
Start the Backend:
Run the command:
bash
npm start
You should see:
Server running in development mode on port 3000
Visit: http://localhost:3000
MongoDB Connected: ...
